---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - Disendarkenment" description="Privacy policy for psychedelic journey facilitation services, including HIPAA compliance and data protection measures.">
	<section class="py-16 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
				<p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

				<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						Disendarkenment ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy and maintaining the confidentiality of your personal and health information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our psychedelic journey facilitation services.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. HIPAA Compliance</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						As a healthcare service provider, we comply with the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) and maintain strict standards for protecting your protected health information (PHI). Your health information is treated with the highest level of confidentiality and security.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. Information We Collect</h2>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Personal Information</h3>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Name, address, phone number, and email address</li>
						<li>Date of birth and identification information</li>
						<li>Emergency contact information</li>
						<li>Insurance information (if applicable)</li>
					</ul>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Health Information</h3>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li>Medical history and current health conditions</li>
						<li>Psychiatric history and mental health information</li>
						<li>Current medications and supplements</li>
						<li>Previous psychedelic experiences</li>
						<li>Session notes and treatment records</li>
						<li>Progress and outcome information</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
						We use your information for the following purposes:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li>Providing psychedelic journey facilitation services</li>
						<li>Conducting safety screenings and assessments</li>
						<li>Planning and delivering personalized treatment</li>
						<li>Monitoring your progress and outcomes</li>
						<li>Ensuring compliance with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
						<li>Communicating with you about your treatment</li>
						<li>Billing and payment processing</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
						We may share your information only in the following circumstances:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li><strong>With your written consent:</strong> We will obtain your authorization before sharing information</li>
						<li><strong>For treatment purposes:</strong> With other healthcare providers involved in your care</li>
						<li><strong>Legal requirements:</strong> When required by law or court order</li>
						<li><strong>Safety concerns:</strong> To prevent serious harm to you or others</li>
						<li><strong>Regulatory compliance:</strong> To state licensing boards or regulatory agencies</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Data Security</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
						We implement comprehensive security measures to protect your information:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li>Encrypted data storage and transmission</li>
						<li>Secure, password-protected systems</li>
						<li>Limited access on a need-to-know basis</li>
						<li>Regular security audits and updates</li>
						<li>Staff training on privacy and security protocols</li>
						<li>Physical security measures for paper records</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. Your Rights</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
						Under HIPAA and applicable privacy laws, you have the right to:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li>Access and review your health information</li>
						<li>Request corrections to your records</li>
						<li>Request restrictions on use or disclosure</li>
						<li>Request confidential communications</li>
						<li>File a complaint about privacy practices</li>
						<li>Receive a copy of this privacy notice</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Record Retention</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						We retain your health records for the period required by law and professional standards, typically 7-10 years after your last service date. Records are securely destroyed when no longer required.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. Website and Digital Privacy</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
						Our website may collect:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li>Basic usage analytics (anonymized)</li>
						<li>Contact form submissions</li>
						<li>Cookies for website functionality</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						We do not sell or share website data with third parties for marketing purposes.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. Minors</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						Our services are only provided to adults 21 years and older. We do not knowingly collect information from minors.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of significant changes and post the updated policy on our website.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">12. Contact Information</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						For questions about this Privacy Policy or to exercise your privacy rights, contact:
					</p>
					<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							<strong>Privacy Officer</strong><br>
							Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@disendarkenment.com" class="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800">privacy@disendarkenment.com</a><br>
							Phone: Available upon request<br>
							Address: Licensed facilities in Oregon and Colorado
						</p>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">13. Complaints</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
						If you believe your privacy rights have been violated, you may file a complaint with:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-6 space-y-2">
						<li>Our Privacy Officer (contact information above)</li>
						<li>The U.S. Department of Health and Human Services</li>
						<li>Applicable state regulatory agencies</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
						You will not be retaliated against for filing a complaint.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>